[07:53.94]	His glorious deeds for my indignities.
[07:57.02]	Percy is but my factor, good my lord,
[07:59.95]	To engross up glorious deeds on my behalf;
[08:03.31]	And I will call him to so strict account,
[08:06.59]	That he shall render every glory up,
[08:09.52]	Yea, even the slightest worship of his time,
[08:12.95]	Or I will tear the reckoning from his heart.
[08:16.44]	This, in the name of God, I promise here:
[08:19.59]	The which if He be pleased I shall perform,
[08:23.01]	I do beseech your majesty may salve
[08:25.95]	The long-grown wounds of my intemperance:
